e6bb81ce-57ad-5fbf-a807-7e688fe61044,tg:rubgr:896,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"Bruegel & Schongauer. [Otto] Benesch, Ren. in North Eur.[= The Art of the Renaissance in Northern Europe : Its Relation to the Contemporary Spiritual and Intellectual Movements, Cambridge,Mass.: s.n. 1945], p. 94; noticed that the London Epiphany Joseph & his neighbour are derived from Schongauer's Epiphany (Bartsch 6 [= Adam von Bartsch, Le peintre graveur, Vienne: Degen, 1808-1821]). [toegevoegde vermelding]: To which I add: 1) Death & Virgin: bed curtain arrangement and foreshortening derived from Schongauer's Death of Virgin : B.33; 2) Slight relations in Christ Carrying the Cross to Schongauer. Bartsch 21 ; Ortelius hatte Zeichnungen von der Kupferstichpresse von Schongauer.",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>Bruegel & Schongauer. [Otto] Benesch, Ren. in North Eur.[= The Art of the Renaissance in Northern Europe : Its Relation to the Contemporary Spiritual and Intellectual Movements, Cambridge,Mass.: s.n. 1945], p. 94; noticed that the London Epiphany Joseph & his neighbour are derived from Schongauer's Epiphany (Bartsch 6 [= Adam von Bartsch, Le peintre graveur, Vienne: Degen, 1808-1821]). [toegevoegde vermelding]: To which I add: 1) Death & Virgin: bed curtain arrangement and foreshortening derived from Schongauer's Death of Virgin : B.33; 2) Slight relations in Christ Carrying the Cross to Schongauer. Bartsch 21 ; Ortelius hatte Zeichnungen von der Kupferstichpresse von Schongauer.</content>
